How a Request Flows
Let's say a user logs in.

Frontend
?
??? Login.tsx
?
?
authService.ts
?
?
POST /login
?
Backend
?
?
api/auth.py
?
?
auth_service.py
?
?
User Model
?
?
PostgreSQL

Each layer has a clear responsibility:
    • Page: Displays the UI. 
    • Service (frontend): Sends the request. 
    • API route: Receives the request. 
    • Service (backend): Contains the business logic. 
    • Model: Represents the database. 
    • Database: Stores the data.
This way, all the code for a feature lives together, making it easier to navigate as the application grows. Many modern FastAPI and larger production applications favor this organization because you spend less time jumping between directories when working on a specific feature. 
